headline.main: Juppe Says No to French Presidential Bid but Slams Candidate Fillon
headline.print_headline: Juppe Says No to French Presidential Bid but Slams Candidate Fillon

lead_paragraph: Former French prime minister Alain Juppe on Monday ruled out replacing scandal-hit Francois Fillon in the coming presidential election but offered no alternative candidates, leaving conservative heavyweights scrambling to find a way to get their party back in the race.
